        }
      ]
    },
    "Management": {
      "text": "See\nHemoptysis\nMassive: intubate (ideally ETT >8.0), angio or bronch to identify and stop localized source, consider nebulized\nTXA\nCorrect\ncoagulopathy\nMethylprednisolone\n1g +\nplasmapheresis\nSee\nGlomerulonephritis\n, consult nephrology\nPlasmapheresis\nshown to be beneficial\n[1]\nIn severe cases may need:\nRheumatology eval: Immunosuppressants",
      "subsections": {},
